Initial processing of loaded data. Please select whether MBR has been switched on and what type of DIA-NN output are you using. This will adjust the columns to be filtered the report on.%%00010%%00010First, low quality peptides are filtered out. Filtering occurs based on the q-values and values in the Quantity.Quality column. Next, precursors are pivotted on the stripped sequence level and further are grouped on PG level using maximum values for all intensity columns and minimal values for all types of q-values. The total quantity sum is calculated for every PG and peptide. PG level table represents the first output of this metanode, the second one is the table on the stripped peptide sequence level.%%00010The third output of this metanode are individual sample names. These names can be changed in the following steps, if necessary for better visualization experience.%%00010%%00010Please, inspect the metanode inner structure for more details - doubleclick on the metanode while holding the Ctrl key or rigth clicking on it, go to the Component menu and select Open.%%00010%%00010=================%%00010%%00010Used programs and tools and their respective licenses at the time of the metanode creation.
